[{"question":"Now when you saw the car, what did it tell you about what may have happened here?","answer":"It told me something was really wrong.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":55,"aSentId":56},{"question":"Do you think he has it in him to keep safe in an environment, in the one that he\u0027s in now?","answer":"Well, Piers, he\u0027s a tough kid, he\u0027s in great shape, and he\u0027s really smart, but I\u0027m afraid that he\u0027s not geared up for this environment.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":67,"aSentId":68},{"question":"What would you like to say to him?","answer":"I would say, hey, we all make mistakes and it doesn\u0027t matter how far out you are, or what\u0027s happened, we want you to come home.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":80,"aSentId":81},{"question":"When you hear a story like the one I\u0027ve just described about Jonathan Croom, and you see the anguish of his farther, it must bring back very vivid memories for both of you?","answer":"Yes, those memories never die, of course, and we wanted to just talk to Mr. Croom.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":96,"aSentId":97},{"question":"And what do you say to youngsters who want to follow him -- in Christopher\u0027s footsteps like that?","answer":".","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":127,"aSentId":128},{"question":"Realistically, how easy is it to survive in that situation?","answer":"Well, you know, it really depends on what you start with in terms of your physical health and what resources you have.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":148,"aSentId":149},{"question":"Do you believe there is a link?","answer":"Well, I think common sense would have you think, certainly in the case of this 8-year-old boy, that there is some sort of association here.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":176,"aSentId":177},{"question":"What do you think of that phenomenon amongst young people these days?","answer":"Yes, I mean, and I\u0027ve seen this before.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":204,"aSentId":205},{"question":"What do you make of it, now that you\u0027ve had a bit of time to really assess it?","answer":"Well, I still think it goes back to his childhood trauma.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":221,"aSentId":222},{"question":"Is there enough being done either at the state level or federal level to tackle what many think is the root cause behind so much of the violence?","answer":"I completely agree.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":233,"aSentId":234},{"question":"So, George Tunis, tell me why you came up with this or why you think it would work?","answer":"Our company is an armor company, full of engineers, and throughout the war and several Darfur contracts we were able to create armor that protected our troops overseas.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":271,"aSentId":272},{"question":"Can it stop an AR-15 in the hands of somebody like Adam Lanza?","answer":"We make all levels of armor, so the armor that we\u0027ve outfitted many school with -- schools with is NIJ Level 3A, so that\u0027s exactly the same armor that would be in a police vest.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":284,"aSentId":285},{"question":"Are you supportive of this?","answer":"Yes, I am.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":292,"aSentId":293},{"question":"I mean, my argument would be, how does this stop somebody like Adam Lanza with an AR-15 and a hundred bullet magazine, for example?","answer":"It\u0027s a great question.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":297,"aSentId":298},{"question":"But you\u0027re doing more for genuinely bulletproof doors?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":331,"aSentId":332},{"question":"And this is the kind of thing you\u0027re talking about?","answer":"Well, this is -- not -- you know, this is shop (ph) -- we make corporate room ballistic doors out of this.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":333,"aSentId":334},{"question":"ORGAN: Are they -- are they prohibitively (ph) expensive?","answer":"No.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":344,"aSentId":345},{"question":"So schools around America could have these relatively cheaply?","answer":"I think so, yes.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":346,"aSentId":347},{"question":"Are you a parent yourself?","answer":"I have two kids in school.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":349,"aSentId":350},{"question":"How do you feel about my just concern about the militarizing of -- of educational process to kids?","answer":"You know, I think kids should be able to go to school in a -- in an environment that is not full of fear.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":351,"aSentId":352},{"question":"And would that door, would that substance stop an AR-15?","answer":"No, this -- this door would not.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":362,"aSentId":363},{"question":"He\u0027s supportive of a military strike against Syria and its regime?","answer":"I think at this point, when America says there\u0027s a thin red line in the international community, most civilized nations agree with that.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":433,"aSentId":434},{"question":"Why?","answer":"I didn\u0027t say they got the story wrong.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":470,"aSentId":471},{"question":"What is your response to that?","answer":"You know, I actually was hoping to see this movie.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":507,"aSentId":508},{"question":"Steve jobs?","answer":"Ashton Kutcher\u0027s impression of Jobs.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":528,"aSentId":529},{"question":"What?","answer":"Get your (inaudible) feet (ph) out.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":538,"aSentId":539},{"question":"What are you going to do, you\u0027re going to fire me?","answer":"No, I already fired you.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":542,"aSentId":543},{"question":"Is that like Steve Jobs?","answer":"There were a lot of incidences of Steve Jobs\u0027 history that were like that.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":545,"aSentId":546},{"question":"Are you hoping the Aaron Sorkin (ph) version, the -- the movie that he is bringing out about Steve Jobs will be a little bit more realistic?","answer":"I was hoping this movie would be, a, realistic or if not realistic, it\u0027s very excited and entertaining.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":549,"aSentId":550},{"question":"You haven\u0027t flown since 9/11, right?","answer":"I\u0027m the wrong person to ask.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":562,"aSentId":563},{"question":"How many hours of sleep do you need in life, Steve?","answer":"It depends.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":575,"aSentId":576},{"question":"Does that actually happen?","answer":"It happened a lot in the old days.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":587,"aSentId":588},{"question":"Well, what do and Kanye talk about?","answer":"You know, we had some nice discussions about some of his ideas for a business he sees.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":611,"aSentId":612},{"question":"You\u0027ve got $2 bills?","answer":"Yes, Steve Wozniak, one of my favorite guests.","docId":"130826pmt","qSentId":625,"aSentId":626}]